data.message: I was always a harsh critic of Coach McCarthy, mostly as a play caller. I felt in 2010, especially in the playoffs, he was more aggressive and we really would put our foot on the gas. However; these past few years I thought we had the offense to have those 50+ point games, like we did against Chicago and Philly, every week and yet we didn't push the limits. So I'm excited to see if Clements will add more aggressive play calling to our offense. All that being said, Coach McCarthy has proven himself to be an amazing HC. It feels like this season he will finally add a little spark to his personality that has been lacking. Hopefully without the play calling duties he will me more tuned in to the pulse of the team. data.name: Tracing the roots of players riding bikes

data.message: Oh wow!  What a great article.  I had no idea how important this picture was when I bought it.  My grandfather used to talk about riding the kids bikes and how neat the relationship between the team and community was.   Green Bay is a special place, and the Packers are a special team.  Go Pack!

James Lofton, Ezra Johnson, Jim Gueno, Eddie Lee Ivory, Mark Koncar.  All guys who rode my bikes in 79, 80, 81.

Don't tell my parents.... 
I lived by Bellin/St Vincent on east side.  We used to take off,  ride our bikes across the train bridge, down Broadway to Lombardi.  Lombardi to practice field.

My dad lived in Stevens Point, WI in the 1950s when the Packers had training camp. It was 6 blocks from the dorms to the field and Lombardi wouldn't get a bus to transport the players.  It was conditioning.  Some kids from Point would let the players borrow their bikes and they would retrieve overthrown passes at practice.

I have to say i tried to find the players in the mid to late 70's and never could.. Mean Jo Green wass so real and so attainable.. although at the time the packers werent very good, I lived less than a mile away and would ride through the parking lot all the time!

That is why the Packers are so special.  They love their fans and the kids whose bikes they ride will remember it for a lifetime and just seeing the smiles on their faces.  Holding the helmets of the player and walking or running beside unless there is room on the back of the bike and they can stand up on it.  Love them Packers.  No other team does anything like this.  Many have copied the Lambeau Leap though, that really sucks.  They should be penalized for doing it?  LOL.
They rode my bike back in 1963!
Jerry Kramer . Did you ever ride bike to practice field. What would Vince say? Lol
At St. Norbert College Elijah Pitts rode my bike while I sat on the (butterfly) handlebars.  Late 1960s.
How does this whole bike thing work. Do you go and hope they pick your child's bike???

That is my house right between the two "walkers". My ride was Scott Hunter when I was a kid. I had my picture taken during one bike ride with him, and it appeared in at least 3 different newspapers across the state. I got a glossy of it and had him sign it - I have it packed away somewhere!
